2
00:00:59.018 --> 00:01:00.436
Come here.

3
00:01:05.167 --> 00:01:06.459
You know me?

4
00:01:06.484 --> 00:01:07.777
Everyone knows you.

5
00:01:10.221 --> 00:01:11.744
You know Young Jun?

6
00:01:14.755 --> 00:01:16.580
Tell him it's time.

7
00:01:18.472 --> 00:01:19.473
Go.

8
00:01:47.650 --> 00:01:49.569
What's going on here?

9
00:02:00.371 --> 00:02:01.497
Hey. how's it going?

10
00:02:07.790 --> 00:02:09.123
You guys seem to
have wandered off

11
00:02:09.148 --> 00:02:10.566
Long Zii territory.

12
00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:11.799
It's okay.

13
00:02:11.824 --> 00:02:13.424
We all get turned
around now and then.

14
00:02:14.260 --> 00:02:16.303
I'd be happy to point you
in the right direction.

15
00:02:16.304 --> 00:02:18.306
You're the one who's turned
around. motherfucker.

16
00:02:19.599 --> 00:02:21.016
Wow. you escalated
that pretty fast.

17
00:02:21.017 --> 00:02:22.726
Usually there's a
little more repartee.

18
00:02:22.727 --> 00:02:23.564
a few zingers

19
00:02:23.589 --> 00:02:24.964
before the hatchets
come out. you know?

20
00:02:24.989 --> 00:02:26.199
Walk away. asshole.

21
00:02:27.663 --> 00:02:30.665
We fought the ducks
together for one day.

22
00:02:30.690 --> 00:02:32.658
Now Mai Ling thinks she
can just set up opium dens

23
00:02:32.683 --> 00:02:34.142
in Hop Wei territory?

24
00:02:34.167 --> 00:02:35.959
That's against the treaty.

25
00:02:35.984 --> 00:02:39.737
And. you know.
basic common sense.

26
00:02:39.762 --> 00:02:43.098
So take your molasses.
get the fuck out of here.

27
00:02:43.140 --> 00:02:44.432
or I'll take it.

28
00:02:44.457 --> 00:02:46.124
and then you'll have
to explain to Mai Ling

29
00:02:46.125 --> 00:02:49.503
how you lost your opium
and got your asses kicked.

30
00:02:57.094 --> 00:02:58.429
Huh.

31
00:03:00.723 --> 00:03:02.682
Still gonna feed you that
hatchet in three seconds.

32
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.767
Listen to me. you dumb fuck...

33
00:03:03.768 --> 00:03:04.935
- Two.
- I don't know what you think

34
00:03:04.936 --> 00:03:05.977
- is gonna happen here.
- One.

35
00:03:05.978 --> 00:03:06.938
It's not gonna end well.

36
00:04:16.465 --> 00:04:18.091
- All right. let's go. boys!
- Yeah!

37
00:04:18.092 --> 00:04:19.926
Let's go get 'em!

38
00:04:19.927 --> 00:04:21.720
Now. boys. Let's go!

39
00:04:21.721 --> 00:04:22.847
Come on.

40
00:05:48.849 --> 00:05:49.974
Hey. how's it going?

41
00:05:49.975 --> 00:05:51.351
You know there's a
door right there.

42
00:05:51.352 --> 00:05:52.937
Shut up and help me up.

43
00:07:56.769 --> 00:07:59.479
San Francisco police!

44
00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:00.940
Stand down!

45
00:08:09.782 --> 00:08:11.074
Hey!

46
00:08:11.075 --> 00:08:11.992
Get up!

47
00:08:15.704 --> 00:08:19.207
Police! Hold your
ground! Hold your ground!

48
00:08:19.208 --> 00:08:20.708
Ah Sahm!

49
00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:22.710
Don't move.

50
00:08:22.711 --> 00:08:24.338
Put your hands
where I can see 'em.

51
00:08:27.091 --> 00:08:28.731
It's not my hands you
have to worry about.

52
00:08:29.927 --> 00:08:31.261
Yeah?

53
00:08:31.262 --> 00:08:34.098
You think you can kick
faster than a 12-gauge?

54
00:08:36.517 --> 00:08:38.434
They finally put this
place back together.

55
00:08:38.435 --> 00:08:39.978
and you and the Long
Zii are out here

56
00:08:39.979 --> 00:08:41.020
tearing it apart again.

57
00:08:41.021 --> 00:08:43.815
You're the one coming in here
every day with an army of cops.

58
00:08:43.816 --> 00:08:45.066
busting heads.

59
00:08:45.067 --> 00:08:46.776
Because it's fucking chaos here.

60
00:08:46.777 --> 00:08:49.570
Only since you cops started
cracking down in Chinatown.

61
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.364
Hey. I was here during that riot

62
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:53.032
trying to keep your people safe.

63
00:08:53.033 --> 00:08:56.411
We don't need you
to keep us safe.

64
00:08:56.412 --> 00:08:58.332
We need you to stay the
hell out of our business.

65
00:08:58.706 --> 00:08:59.956
Tong business.

66
00:08:59.957 --> 00:09:01.624
I mean every business
the cops have shut down

67
00:09:01.625 --> 00:09:03.751
with these bullshit ordinances.

68
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:04.962
People are starving.

69
00:09:05.504 --> 00:09:07.631
And how are your turf
wars gonna feed them?

70
00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:10.259
Fuck's sake!

71
00:09:12.261 --> 00:09:13.261
Get the fuck out of here.

72
00:09:17.391 --> 00:09:18.600
Little shit.

73
00:09:20.728 --> 00:09:23.313
Stone. no shooting!
We're pulling out.

74
00:09:23.314 --> 00:09:25.106
- What are you talking about?
- Fight's over.

75
00:09:25.107 --> 00:09:26.607
We're not here to
start it up again.

76
00:09:26.608 --> 00:09:29.444
Come on! Let's fall back!

77
00:09:29.445 --> 00:09:30.779
Fuck. Bill.

78
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:32.906
Something on your mind?

79
00:09:33.991 --> 00:09:35.575
Ever since the chief kicked it.

80
00:09:35.576 --> 00:09:37.285
you've had your eye
on his damn job.

81
00:09:37.286 --> 00:09:39.955
And you're tying our fucking
hands behind our backs.

82
00:09:40.998 --> 00:09:42.998
You sure you wanna speak
to the new chief that way?

83
00:09:44.460 --> 00:09:45.502
You're not him yet.

84
00:11:31.733 --> 00:11:34.445
And where is Mr. Greer? Hmm?

85
00:11:35.779 --> 00:11:36.905
Hey. Greer!

86
00:11:41.076 --> 00:11:42.161
Greer!

87
00:11:59.678 --> 00:12:01.095
Mr. Greer.

88
00:12:01.096 --> 00:12:03.098
So good to see you again.

89
00:12:06.768 --> 00:12:09.146
- 100 for the lot?
- As agreed.

90
00:12:11.648 --> 00:12:12.940
They look kinda old.

91
00:12:12.941 --> 00:12:14.901
100. you get old.

92
00:12:14.902 --> 00:12:16.819
200. you get new.

93
00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:19.323
I say this. You choose 100.

94
00:12:20.532 --> 00:12:21.450
I know what I chose.

95
00:12:22.117 --> 00:12:23.534
I just wanna make
sure they work.

96
00:12:23.535 --> 00:12:25.162
I test all myself.

97
00:12:25.746 --> 00:12:26.913
Oh. yeah?

98
00:12:26.914 --> 00:12:28.665
And I'm supposed to
take your word for it?

99
00:12:36.548 --> 00:12:37.423
Hey.

100
00:12:37.424 --> 00:12:39.926
"Hey" what?

101
00:12:39.927 --> 00:12:42.387
Think anyone's gonna
miss one uppity Chinaman?

102
00:12:44.723 --> 00:12:46.183
You got something to say?

103
00:12:48.852 --> 00:12:50.520
One...

104
00:12:50.521 --> 00:12:52.188
hundred...

105
00:12:52.189 --> 00:12:53.607
dollar.

106
00:13:00.489 --> 00:13:02.950
You're one ballsy Chinaman.
I'll give you that.

107
00:13:07.746 --> 00:13:09.998
"One hundred dollar."

108
00:13:19.925 --> 00:13:21.593
Now get the fuck out of here.

109
00:13:48.161 --> 00:13:50.955
[in Cantonese]
These fucking bulls.

110
00:13:50.956 --> 00:13:52.915
Suddenly you can't throw
a stick in Chinatown

111
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:54.710
without hitting one.

112
00:13:55.127 --> 00:13:58.045
[in English] Used to be the
Chinatown squad was a joke.

113
00:13:58.046 --> 00:14:00.172
Now they got half the police
force cracking skulls.

114
00:14:00.173 --> 00:14:01.382
It's all politics.

115
00:14:01.383 --> 00:14:04.595
Ducks are just trying to look
tough before the election.

116
00:14:06.847 --> 00:14:07.972
Yeah. but why they
gotta shut down

117
00:14:07.973 --> 00:14:09.640
all my favorite spots. though?

118
00:14:09.641 --> 00:14:11.684
I finally find a
decent egg tart.

119
00:14:11.685 --> 00:14:14.353
and bang. Mr. Gaoyuan
is gone. man.

120
00:14:14.354 --> 00:14:16.063
Meanwhile. Mai Ling
breaks the treaty

121
00:14:16.064 --> 00:14:17.356
and we can't even retaliate

122
00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:18.983
because of all these damn bulls.

123
00:14:18.984 --> 00:14:22.653
We're losing protection
money and we're losing guys.

124
00:14:22.654 --> 00:14:25.740
Either we find a way to
dodge these ordinances

125
00:14:25.741 --> 00:14:27.909
- or we're fucked.
- Yeah.

126
00:14:43.175 --> 00:14:45.801
Young Jun.

127
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.762
I am. uh. honored.

128
00:14:47.763 --> 00:14:51.891
And I am. uh. pissed off.

129
00:14:51.892 --> 00:14:54.185
I'm only here because my men
have come up empty-handed

130
00:14:54.186 --> 00:14:55.561
two weeks in a row.

131
00:14:55.562 --> 00:14:57.855
I know. and I'm sorry.

132
00:14:57.856 --> 00:15:01.025
but the bulls shut us down
twice in the last month.

133
00:15:01.026 --> 00:15:02.652
These are tough
times for all of us.

134
00:15:02.653 --> 00:15:05.363
But that doesn't
absolve us of our debts.

135
00:15:05.364 --> 00:15:08.866
I'm happy to pay for
the protection. but...

136
00:15:08.867 --> 00:15:11.786
I don't see that
we're protected now.

137
00:15:11.787 --> 00:15:13.913
Do you really wanna
talk to me like that?

138
00:15:13.914 --> 00:15:16.123
I don't have the
money to pay you.

139
00:15:16.124 --> 00:15:18.876
I'm just telling you how it is.

140
00:15:18.877 --> 00:15:21.004
Your father would've understood.

141
00:15:24.216 --> 00:15:26.092
My father isn't
running things anymore.

142
00:15:26.093 --> 00:15:27.385
I am.

143
00:15:27.386 --> 00:15:28.552
So if I were you. I'd leave him

144
00:15:28.553 --> 00:15:30.179
the fuck out of
this conversation.

145
00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:31.722
If he could see you now...

146
00:15:31.723 --> 00:15:33.057
This fucking onion.

147
00:15:33.058 --> 00:15:34.308
Hey. let's...

148
00:15:34.309 --> 00:15:36.977
Let's let Hong handle this. huh?

149
00:15:36.978 --> 00:15:39.063
It's okay. You're the boss.

150
00:15:39.064 --> 00:15:41.692
You shouldn't be
collecting anyway...

151
00:15:44.903 --> 00:15:47.405
Boss.

152
00:15:47.406 --> 00:15:49.198
You better watch the way
you fucking talk to me.

153
00:15:49.199 --> 00:15:51.118
old man.

154
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:04.005
Handle it.

155
00:16:05.757 --> 00:16:07.634
Young Jun. Hey. hey.

156
00:16:08.468 --> 00:16:09.720
What the fuck was that?

157
00:16:10.595 --> 00:16:11.595
What?

158
00:16:11.596 --> 00:16:14.056
Getting in my way like that!

159
00:16:14.057 --> 00:16:15.433
You were beating on an old man.

160
00:16:15.434 --> 00:16:18.060
I was making a fucking point.

161
00:16:18.061 --> 00:16:19.478
He disrespected me.

162
00:16:19.479 --> 00:16:21.355
You want respect.

163
00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:23.596
you're not gonna get it by
flying off the fucking handle.

164
00:16:24.818 --> 00:16:27.654
Don't you ever challenge
me in public again.

165
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:35.244
<i>It's getting
dangerous out there.</i>

166
00:16:35.245 --> 00:16:36.454
Fuck.

167
00:16:36.455 --> 00:16:38.622
The bulls are coming
in larger numbers.

168
00:16:38.623 --> 00:16:42.084
shutting down businesses.
damaging our property.

169
00:16:42.085 --> 00:16:44.462
Our unity might be the
only weapon we have

170
00:16:44.463 --> 00:16:45.547
against this enemy.

171
00:16:46.882 --> 00:16:49.049
The Jiang Yao Tong
has always enjoyed

172
00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:51.635
a friendship with the Long Zii.

173
00:16:51.636 --> 00:16:54.764
But the truth is. the
more tongs there are.

174
00:16:54.765 --> 00:16:57.183
the more we are divided.

175
00:16:57.184 --> 00:17:00.519
And so as you asked

176
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:03.814
and under the terms
you stipulated.

177
00:17:03.815 --> 00:17:08.236
the Jiang Yao Tong are honored
to become part of the Long Zii.

178
00:17:14.534 --> 00:17:18.788
We pledge our blades. our blood.

179
00:17:18.789 --> 00:17:22.541
and our souls to the Long
Zii and to its leader.

180
00:17:22.542 --> 00:17:23.960
Mai Ling.

181
00:17:32.385 --> 00:17:33.845
Kong Pak.

182
00:17:42.479 --> 00:17:44.855
After leading a
tong for so long.

183
00:17:44.856 --> 00:17:47.109
I'm sure this was
not an easy decision.

184
00:17:48.276 --> 00:17:50.069
It wasn't.

185
00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:52.947
But when you're given no choice.

186
00:17:52.948 --> 00:17:55.200
the choice becomes clear.

187
00:18:00.622 --> 00:18:03.542
Li Yong tells me you're
a great warrior...

188
00:18:05.502 --> 00:18:07.045
And an honorable man.

189
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:12.509
I hope you will sit on my
council with the elders.

190
00:18:18.098 --> 00:18:19.641
It would be my honor.

191
00:18:27.315 --> 00:18:28.650
Well. then...

192
00:18:34.072 --> 00:18:35.699
Welcome to the Long Zii.

193
00:19:10.483 --> 00:19:12.902
<i>I am Irish. Dublin-born.</i>

194
00:19:12.903 --> 00:19:15.487
And it pains me.
as I'm sure it does

195
00:19:15.488 --> 00:19:18.490
everyone on this
council. to be unable

196
00:19:18.491 --> 00:19:20.784
to hire Irish labor.

197
00:19:20.785 --> 00:19:23.537
But with lumber prices
bleeding me dry.

198
00:19:23.538 --> 00:19:26.665
I just don't have the margins.

199
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:29.293
If you don't have the
margins to pay a living wage.

200
00:19:29.294 --> 00:19:31.253
you're doing something wrong.

201
00:19:31.254 --> 00:19:33.255
It's a wage the
Chinese can live on.

202
00:19:33.256 --> 00:19:36.008
A dog could live on it too.
but that doesn't make it right.

203
00:19:36.009 --> 00:19:37.426
Mr. Leary. we've
been through this.

204
00:19:37.427 --> 00:19:39.303
If you would simply
study the economics...

205
00:19:39.304 --> 00:19:40.846
I understand the economics.

206
00:19:40.847 --> 00:19:43.474
Well. then why don't
you explain them to me?

207
00:19:43.475 --> 00:19:46.311
Because clearly. we're seeing
the numbers differently.

208
00:19:53.610 --> 00:19:55.569
I'll give you a number.

209
00:19:55.570 --> 00:19:57.696
25.000.

210
00:19:57.697 --> 00:19:59.323
What's that?

211
00:19:59.324 --> 00:20:01.159
That's how many chinks
there are in this city.

212
00:20:02.994 --> 00:20:04.746
And not a single damn
one of them can vote.

213
00:20:07.082 --> 00:20:09.166
Now...

214
00:20:09.167 --> 00:20:10.292
do you happen to know

215
00:20:10.293 --> 00:20:13.003
how many Irish there
are in San Francisco?

216
00:20:13.004 --> 00:20:14.338
I have no idea.

217
00:20:14.339 --> 00:20:16.715
Well. Mr. Buckley does.

218
00:20:16.716 --> 00:20:19.259
He's got that special
election to win.

219
00:20:19.260 --> 00:20:22.429
And I got 30.000 votes
he needs to do it.

220
00:20:22.430 --> 00:20:23.639
How many votes do you have?

221
00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:25.766
Mr. Leary. you've been on
this council long enough

222
00:20:25.767 --> 00:20:28.727
to know we all want the
Chinese gone. but given...

223
00:20:28.728 --> 00:20:30.562
But that won't stop you all

224
00:20:30.563 --> 00:20:32.189
from making every
last buck you can

225
00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:33.482
while they're still here.

226
00:20:33.483 --> 00:20:37.111
If I could show you what I am
paying for steel and lumber...

227
00:20:37.112 --> 00:20:38.737
So negotiate with
your suppliers!

228
00:20:38.738 --> 00:20:40.572
You think I haven't?
It's all I do!

229
00:20:40.573 --> 00:20:41.949
Enough.

230
00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:43.618
We're going round in circles.

231
00:20:45.286 --> 00:20:47.788
That's because no one
ever says anything new.

232
00:20:47.789 --> 00:20:50.124
Welcome to
politics. Mr. Leary.

233
00:20:50.125 --> 00:20:52.001
Now. I move to adjourn.

234
00:20:52.002 --> 00:20:53.502
Seconded.

235
00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:54.713
Fuck.

236
00:20:56.131 --> 00:20:57.464
<i>I've got seniority.</i>

237
00:20:57.465 --> 00:21:00.384
And Flannagan himself
recommended me for the position

238
00:21:00.385 --> 00:21:01.552
before he passed.

239
00:21:01.553 --> 00:21:03.470
So what's Mr. Buckley
waiting for?

240
00:21:03.471 --> 00:21:05.014
He needs a police
chief. doesn't he?

241
00:21:05.015 --> 00:21:08.017
I think he's just
sorting himself out.

242
00:21:08.018 --> 00:21:11.562
He's focused on keeping
his own job right now.

243
00:21:11.563 --> 00:21:13.605
He practically gave you
the keys to the city

244
00:21:13.606 --> 00:21:15.566
when you arrested
that swordsman.

245
00:21:15.567 --> 00:21:18.485
It will happen.
and when it does.

246
00:21:18.486 --> 00:21:20.822
I will be out of
Chinatown for good.

247
00:21:25.201 --> 00:21:26.536
I miss you.

248
00:21:29.998 --> 00:21:31.750
I miss my family.

249
00:21:36.171 --> 00:21:37.297
Please come home.

250
00:21:44.512 --> 00:21:47.474
Get out of Chinatown.
and we can talk about it.

251
00:21:54.189 --> 00:21:57.525
Molly. Michael. Cut
it out right now.

252
00:21:59.861 --> 00:22:00.621
Some whiskey. Bill?

253
00:22:03.990 --> 00:22:05.325
Thank you.

254
00:22:08.453 --> 00:22:09.329
And how did that go?

255
00:22:11.164 --> 00:22:12.916
Okay. I think.

256
00:22:17.212 --> 00:22:18.421
And the chief job?

257
00:22:19.881 --> 00:22:21.841
- Any day now.
- Excellent.

258
00:22:23.593 --> 00:22:25.469
Well. you have a
wonderful family.

259
00:22:25.470 --> 00:22:27.096
but it's a large one.

260
00:22:27.097 --> 00:22:29.349
And I would love to get
these people out of my house.

261
00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:33.560
Michael. stop doing
that to your sister.

262
00:22:33.561 --> 00:22:35.814
Molly. look after your brother.

263
00:22:36.898 --> 00:22:38.649
Headed back to Sonoma?

264
00:22:38.650 --> 00:22:39.859
Just a weekend trip.

265
00:22:41.569 --> 00:22:43.278
So is someone running the
place while you're gone.

266
00:22:43.279 --> 00:22:46.031
or is it on the honor system?

267
00:22:46.032 --> 00:22:48.742
Chao will keep an eye on things.

268
00:22:48.743 --> 00:22:50.954
- Chao?
- Mm-hmm.

269
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:55.166
Yeah. and who is
keeping an eye on him?

270
00:23:00.505 --> 00:23:02.840
Feels like you're gone more
than you're here these days.

271
00:23:02.841 --> 00:23:04.175
Miss me?

272
00:23:06.177 --> 00:23:07.554
Things are getting
worse out there.

273
00:23:08.555 --> 00:23:10.723
I'm of no use to you right now.

274
00:23:14.894 --> 00:23:15.937
How's the shoulder?

275
00:23:16.855 --> 00:23:19.732
Mm. I'm starting to be
able to move it again.

276
00:23:21.609 --> 00:23:23.110
How are things at the Hop Wei?

277
00:23:23.111 --> 00:23:25.028
Not great.

278
00:23:25.029 --> 00:23:26.239
And Young Jun?

279
00:23:30.326 --> 00:23:32.370
Doesn't take a lot to
set him off these days.

280
00:23:33.163 --> 00:23:35.038
Doing what I can to
keep him on point.

281
00:23:35.039 --> 00:23:37.082
If Young Jun can't find
his way as a leader.

282
00:23:37.083 --> 00:23:38.917
there's nothing you
can do about it.

283
00:23:38.918 --> 00:23:42.004
Some things are beyond
even your control.

284
00:23:42.005 --> 00:23:44.466
Yeah. maybe I should just
start leaving town with you.

285
00:23:45.466 --> 00:23:47.177
There's plenty of
room in the carriage.

286
00:24:06.487 --> 00:24:08.363
Mai Ling.

287
00:24:08.364 --> 00:24:10.741
Mr. Buckley.

288
00:24:10.742 --> 00:24:13.160
How goes the campaign?

289
00:24:13.161 --> 00:24:15.287
Running for a position
I already have.

290
00:24:15.288 --> 00:24:17.831
it's a tricky business.

291
00:24:17.832 --> 00:24:19.166
You mean democracy.

292
00:24:19.167 --> 00:24:20.542
Politics.

293
00:24:20.543 --> 00:24:23.128
Glad-handing. Crowd-pleasing.
It's not in my nature.

294
00:24:23.129 --> 00:24:25.088
I'm sure.

295
00:24:25.089 --> 00:24:26.924
You know. if it helps.

296
00:24:26.925 --> 00:24:29.551
an old Chinese
philosopher once said.

297
00:24:29.552 --> 00:24:31.220
"No one is ever defeated

298
00:24:31.221 --> 00:24:33.931
until defeat has been
accepted as reality."

299
00:24:33.932 --> 00:24:35.975
Thank you. It doesn't.

300
00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:39.479
You caused quite a
fracas the other day.

301
00:24:40.688 --> 00:24:42.022
It was a misunderstanding.

302
00:24:42.023 --> 00:24:45.442
You were making a move
into Hop Wei territory.

303
00:24:45.443 --> 00:24:47.319
I'm keeping the
police off your back

304
00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:49.279
as per our arrangement.

305
00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:50.739
but expanding your operations

306
00:24:50.740 --> 00:24:52.241
was never part of the agreement.

307
00:24:52.242 --> 00:24:54.701
Then I'll change our agreement.

308
00:24:54.702 --> 00:24:56.536
You offered me some
Chinese wisdom.

309
00:24:56.537 --> 00:24:59.414
I will offer you some American.

310
00:24:59.415 --> 00:25:00.749
Benjamin Franklin said.

311
00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:03.001
"Necessity never
made a good bargain."

312
00:25:03.002 --> 00:25:05.337
You might think you have
me at a disadvantage

313
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:08.548
with that incriminating
photograph.

314
00:25:08.549 --> 00:25:10.259
but there's only so
far you can push me

315
00:25:10.260 --> 00:25:14.055
before I decide your leverage
isn't worth the price.

316
00:25:16.015 --> 00:25:18.141
No more moves.

317
00:25:18.142 --> 00:25:21.854
No more violence of any kind
until after the election.

318
00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:23.523
Understood.

319
00:25:25.108 --> 00:25:27.234
Believe me.

320
00:25:27.235 --> 00:25:29.903
the Long Zii greatly
value our relationship

321
00:25:29.904 --> 00:25:32.031
with the mayor of San Francisco.

322
00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:38.204
For your campaign.

323
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:46.169
If the glad-handing ever
gets to be too much.

324
00:25:46.170 --> 00:25:48.922
just do what I do.

325
00:25:48.923 --> 00:25:51.551
Imagine your knife
in their throat.

326
00:26:06.149 --> 00:26:08.859
Here you go. boys.

327
00:26:08.860 --> 00:26:10.902
We closed our tab.

328
00:26:10.903 --> 00:26:12.238
This round's on me.

329
00:26:12.947 --> 00:26:14.406
Charity?

330
00:26:14.407 --> 00:26:16.075
It's just a round. Killy.

331
00:26:17.076 --> 00:26:19.203
Wouldn't need your round
if we were working.

332
00:26:21.080 --> 00:26:23.248
I thought the idea of you
joining the city council

333
00:26:23.249 --> 00:26:26.376
was to get rid of the Chinese
and get us all working again.

334
00:26:26.377 --> 00:26:29.629
What the fuck do
you think I'm doing?

335
00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:31.256
You think I like
sitting 'round a table

336
00:26:31.257 --> 00:26:33.051
with those fat fucks
talking down to me?

337
00:26:35.053 --> 00:26:37.013
I can't just force
them to write new laws.

338
00:26:39.057 --> 00:26:41.433
Listen.

339
00:26:41.434 --> 00:26:43.727
It's like anything else. right?

340
00:26:43.728 --> 00:26:45.062
You find the pressure points.

341
00:26:45.063 --> 00:26:47.689
and then you dig your thumbs in.

342
00:26:47.690 --> 00:26:49.524
These things take time.

343
00:26:49.525 --> 00:26:51.360
Ooh. careful there.

344
00:26:51.361 --> 00:26:54.447
You're even starting to
sound like a politician.

345
00:26:55.365 --> 00:26:57.699
You're an asshole when
you're drunk. Killy.

346
00:26:57.700 --> 00:26:59.744
And a cunt when I'm sober.

347
00:27:05.291 --> 00:27:07.167
Whiskey. three glasses.

348
00:27:07.168 --> 00:27:09.461
- Anything else?
- That's all.

349
00:27:09.462 --> 00:27:12.422
What time is it?

350
00:27:12.423 --> 00:27:13.924
Bedtime.

351
00:27:13.925 --> 00:27:15.468
Earn your keep. baby.

352
00:27:18.721 --> 00:27:20.847
Hey!

353
00:27:20.848 --> 00:27:22.728
- You all right?
- I'm all right. I'm all right.

354
00:27:23.601 --> 00:27:25.228
Hey! Come here.

355
00:27:29.023 --> 00:27:30.149
Hey!

356
00:27:31.984 --> 00:27:34.111
Get the fuck off me!

357
00:27:34.112 --> 00:27:36.363
Hey. what are you
doing? He's robbing me!

358
00:27:36.364 --> 00:27:38.073
It's nine drinks
between the two of you.

359
00:27:38.074 --> 00:27:39.408
plus everything you broke.

360
00:27:39.409 --> 00:27:41.076
He didn't pay for
his fucking drinks.

361
00:27:41.077 --> 00:27:42.452
So take that up with him!

362
00:27:42.453 --> 00:27:45.747
Now. I see you in here again.

363
00:27:45.748 --> 00:27:47.874
I'ma hang you up like
Mama's wet washing.

364
00:27:47.875 --> 00:27:49.459
What?

365
00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:50.753
Just go.

366
00:27:52.588 --> 00:27:54.590
- Asshole!
- My hero.

367
00:28:01.431 --> 00:28:03.975
Just keeping the peace.

368
00:28:05.476 --> 00:28:06.727
Richard?

369
00:28:17.572 --> 00:28:19.614
Bad one?

370
00:28:19.615 --> 00:28:21.951
Um. not... not too bad.

371
00:28:44.015 --> 00:28:45.099
What the fuck is this?

372
00:28:57.904 --> 00:29:00.906
Standard hatchet. bevel
blade. U.S. steel.

373
00:29:00.907 --> 00:29:02.866
The Long Zii use these.

374
00:29:02.867 --> 00:29:04.242
And you make it for them.

375
00:29:04.243 --> 00:29:05.952
I didn't make this.

376
00:29:05.953 --> 00:29:07.370
But you do deal with them.

377
00:29:07.371 --> 00:29:09.165
- Hatchets?
- The Long Zii.

378
00:29:10.708 --> 00:29:12.043
I deal with a lot of people.

379
00:29:12.793 --> 00:29:13.920
Hmm.

380
00:29:16.005 --> 00:29:18.798
You sit here drinking
like you're one of us.

381
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:22.636
but tomorrow. you might sell
the blade that kills me.

382
00:29:22.637 --> 00:29:26.223
Or I might save your life.

383
00:29:26.224 --> 00:29:27.974
Your father understood the value

384
00:29:27.975 --> 00:29:30.685
of an independent contractor
with his ear to the streets.

385
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:34.773
My father valued
loyalty above all.

386
00:29:34.774 --> 00:29:35.983
And so do I.

387
00:29:40.112 --> 00:29:43.866
At some point. you're gonna
have to choose a side.

388
00:29:55.461 --> 00:29:58.589
You know. Zing said the
exact same thing to me.

389
00:30:00.841 --> 00:30:03.511
Ask for my help. and I
will happily give it.

390
00:30:06.013 --> 00:30:09.140
But don't threaten me.

391
00:30:09.141 --> 00:30:10.768
Doesn't work.

392
00:30:19.694 --> 00:30:22.153
- Something up?
- I don't trust him.

393
00:30:22.154 --> 00:30:25.115
It's Chao. You pay
and he delivers.

394
00:30:25.116 --> 00:30:27.409
And that's what you trust.

395
00:30:27.410 --> 00:30:29.077
Cause and effect. right?

396
00:30:29.078 --> 00:30:30.412
It's very Buddhist.

397
00:30:30.413 --> 00:30:32.205
You a Buddhist?

398
00:30:32.206 --> 00:30:33.915
Fuck no.

399
00:30:33.916 --> 00:30:35.709
Come on. boss.

400
00:30:35.710 --> 00:30:38.879
You here to fuck with Chao
or to get some sticky?

401
00:30:41.757 --> 00:30:43.092
Hey.

402
00:30:54.437 --> 00:30:57.480
- What was that?
- Just the new boss flexing.

403
00:30:57.481 --> 00:30:59.524
Think he's starting
to get paranoid.

404
00:30:59.525 --> 00:31:00.650
This business about Mai Ling

405
00:31:00.651 --> 00:31:02.235
being your sister
isn't helping matters.

406
00:31:02.236 --> 00:31:03.862
I mean. what'd you
think would happen?

407
00:31:03.863 --> 00:31:05.989
I just didn't figure
she would tell him.

408
00:31:05.990 --> 00:31:07.657
It was a cold and reckless

409
00:31:07.658 --> 00:31:10.493
and ultimately brilliant
move on her part.

410
00:31:10.494 --> 00:31:11.995
Classic Mai Ling.

411
00:31:11.996 --> 00:31:13.830
I think he's still
worried about it.

412
00:31:13.831 --> 00:31:14.874
He should be.

413
00:31:17.001 --> 00:31:18.752
Chao. I am loyal to the tong.

414
00:31:18.753 --> 00:31:21.004
You crossed the
salt to find her.

415
00:31:21.005 --> 00:31:23.423
And she ordered my death.

416
00:31:23.424 --> 00:31:25.176
Family can be complicated.

417
00:31:26.010 --> 00:31:27.594
- Look. if you ask me...
- I didn't.

418
00:31:27.595 --> 00:31:30.180
I don't see you moving
against your own sister.

419
00:31:30.181 --> 00:31:31.515
and neither does Young Jun.

420
00:31:32.141 --> 00:31:33.475
You've gotta keep an eye on him.

421
00:31:33.476 --> 00:31:35.727
He's not his father.

422
00:31:35.728 --> 00:31:36.770
He goes off the wrong way.

423
00:31:36.771 --> 00:31:39.064
he could bring down
the whole tong.

424
00:31:39.065 --> 00:31:41.524
We might not have
to wait that long.

425
00:31:41.525 --> 00:31:43.318
The bulls are bleeding us dry.

426
00:31:43.319 --> 00:31:45.111
We don't have the chop
to pay for our molasses.

427
00:31:45.112 --> 00:31:47.614
and now Happy Jack won't
release the product.

428
00:31:47.615 --> 00:31:49.366
None of which reflects
well on the new boss.

429
00:31:49.367 --> 00:31:50.993
I get it. Hmm.

430
00:31:56.082 --> 00:31:57.917
I may be able to help.

431
00:31:59.251 --> 00:32:00.960
Yeah?

432
00:32:00.961 --> 00:32:03.588
I delivered some shooters
to these guys on the docks.

433
00:32:03.589 --> 00:32:06.049
While I was there. I saw cash.

434
00:32:06.050 --> 00:32:07.300
Piles of it.

435
00:32:07.301 --> 00:32:08.760
We're not thieves. Chao.

436
00:32:08.761 --> 00:32:11.805
Now is exactly the
wrong time to get proud.

437
00:32:11.806 --> 00:32:15.142
Now is the time to adapt or die.

438
00:32:24.819 --> 00:32:26.070
Sergeant O'Hara.

439
00:32:28.614 --> 00:32:29.657
May I have a moment?

440
00:32:31.158 --> 00:32:33.577
Of course. Mr. Mayor.

441
00:32:43.421 --> 00:32:45.380
<i>I know you've been
waiting for news</i>

442
00:32:45.381 --> 00:32:47.757
<i>ever since Chief
Flannagan passed away.</i>

443
00:32:47.758 --> 00:32:49.718
and I appreciate your patience.

444
00:32:49.719 --> 00:32:51.469
Of course. sir.

445
00:32:51.470 --> 00:32:55.808
I know conventional wisdom has
you next in line for chief.

446
00:32:57.560 --> 00:33:02.106
But based on a number of
extenuating factors...

447
00:33:03.315 --> 00:33:05.151
I'm afraid I've had
to go another way.

448
00:33:06.152 --> 00:33:07.403
Another way?

449
00:33:08.237 --> 00:33:11.323
I expect you to be a
professional about this.

450
00:33:19.165 --> 00:33:21.666
Sergeant O'Hara. meet
Colonel Benjamin Atwood.

451
00:33:21.667 --> 00:33:23.960
our new chief of police.

452
00:33:23.961 --> 00:33:25.921
Sergeant.

453
00:33:29.592 --> 00:33:31.176
I'm sorry.

454
00:33:31.177 --> 00:33:32.594
Who the hell is this?

455
00:33:32.595 --> 00:33:35.597
Chief Atwood comes to
us from New York City.

456
00:33:35.598 --> 00:33:37.140
where he was
extremely successful

457
00:33:37.141 --> 00:33:39.559
in bringing to bear his
military experience.

458
00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:42.687
as well as the law. to
clean up their Chinatown.

459
00:33:42.688 --> 00:33:44.773
San Francisco is
nothing like New York.

460
00:33:44.774 --> 00:33:46.024
No.

461
00:33:46.025 --> 00:33:50.279
But the Chinese are the Chinese
everywhere. aren't they?

462
00:33:52.114 --> 00:33:55.408
Mr. Gumm. why don't you show
the chief to his new office?

463
00:33:55.409 --> 00:33:57.453
I'm sure he'd like to
get started right away.

464
00:34:09.548 --> 00:34:11.508
That job was mine.

465
00:34:11.509 --> 00:34:13.511
Only in your mind.

466
00:34:15.805 --> 00:34:17.806
I'm facing an election.

467
00:34:17.807 --> 00:34:19.891
and a significant
pillar of my platform

468
00:34:19.892 --> 00:34:22.185
is bringing order to Chinatown.

469
00:34:22.186 --> 00:34:24.145
And that riot left
our citizens shaken.

470
00:34:24.146 --> 00:34:25.563
wondering how
vulnerable they are

471
00:34:25.564 --> 00:34:27.607
to savage foreigners
living in their midst.

472
00:34:27.608 --> 00:34:30.401
And I am the one who
brought order to that riot.

473
00:34:30.402 --> 00:34:31.778
Maybe.

474
00:34:31.779 --> 00:34:33.571
But I would argue that
the entire thing happened

475
00:34:33.572 --> 00:34:35.824
because you failed to
transport a single prisoner...

476
00:34:35.825 --> 00:34:38.618
The man who murdered
our mayor. I might add.

477
00:34:38.619 --> 00:34:40.245
It's not as simple as
that. and you know it.

478
00:34:40.246 --> 00:34:41.704
The voters don't want excuses.

479
00:34:41.705 --> 00:34:43.081
They want results.

480
00:34:43.082 --> 00:34:44.874
And Atwood gets results.

481
00:34:44.875 --> 00:34:46.334
He will tear Chinatown apart

482
00:34:46.335 --> 00:34:48.253
and put the fear of God
into those heathens.

483
00:34:48.254 --> 00:34:50.755
He's an outsider.
These are my men.

484
00:34:50.756 --> 00:34:52.674
You can't expect them
to just follow him.

485
00:34:52.675 --> 00:34:54.801
He brought some of his
own men from New York.

486
00:34:54.802 --> 00:34:57.345
The rest will take
their cues from you.

487
00:34:57.346 --> 00:34:59.013
and if you can't
deliver those cues.

488
00:34:59.014 --> 00:35:00.723
you can deliver me
your resignation

489
00:35:00.724 --> 00:35:01.851
by the end of the day.

490
00:35:03.185 --> 00:35:03.936
Sergeant.

491
00:36:07.207 --> 00:36:08.875
I've been waiting for you.

492
00:36:08.876 --> 00:36:11.711
I come as early as I can.

493
00:36:11.712 --> 00:36:12.546
Oh!

494
00:36:13.547 --> 00:36:14.787
[in Cantonese]
How are you. Lai?

495
00:36:17.593 --> 00:36:19.637
Yes. I'll be staying
for a few days.

496
00:36:21.221 --> 00:36:22.348
Mm!

497
00:36:27.394 --> 00:36:28.395
Come inside.

498
00:36:34.235 --> 00:36:37.445
You see black on wall?

499
00:36:37.446 --> 00:36:39.656
This from fire.

500
00:36:39.657 --> 00:36:40.908
You remember riot?

501
00:36:42.242 --> 00:36:44.702
After the mayor die.

502
00:36:44.703 --> 00:36:46.454
many fire.

503
00:36:46.455 --> 00:36:47.705
Yes.

504
00:36:47.706 --> 00:36:50.583
That was a horrible time.

505
00:36:50.584 --> 00:36:52.835
But Chinese people work hard.

506
00:36:52.836 --> 00:36:55.421
Build back their home. hmm?

507
00:36:55.422 --> 00:36:57.590
It should never have happened.

508
00:36:57.591 --> 00:37:00.718
Well. they did kill the mayor.

509
00:37:00.719 --> 00:37:02.680
Frannie!

510
00:37:09.979 --> 00:37:12.439
Very sad what happen
to your mayor.

511
00:37:13.065 --> 00:37:15.858
Maybe a Chinese man kill him.

512
00:37:15.859 --> 00:37:17.236
Maybe not.

513
00:37:19.905 --> 00:37:21.531
There bad Chinese people

514
00:37:21.532 --> 00:37:25.494
and maybe bad white
people too. no?

515
00:37:26.954 --> 00:37:30.456
But most of us good.

516
00:37:30.457 --> 00:37:33.209
right?

517
00:37:33.210 --> 00:37:34.753
- Of course.
- Of course.

518
00:37:38.215 --> 00:37:39.466
This way!

519
00:37:53.188 --> 00:37:55.189
Please meet Mai Ling.

520
00:37:55.190 --> 00:37:58.152
Very successful
businesswoman in Chinatown.

521
00:38:00.946 --> 00:38:02.488
Oh. my.

522
00:38:02.489 --> 00:38:04.240
She's really beautiful.

523
00:38:04.241 --> 00:38:05.908
Thank you.

524
00:38:05.909 --> 00:38:06.952
So are you.

525
00:38:07.619 --> 00:38:10.580
Would you like to come
inside and have some tea?

526
00:38:10.581 --> 00:38:12.582
I've just finished renovating.

527
00:38:12.583 --> 00:38:15.294
and it's been ages since
I've had any guests.

528
00:38:16.420 --> 00:38:18.005
You speak like an American.

529
00:38:20.382 --> 00:38:21.508
When in Rome.

530
00:38:23.594 --> 00:38:25.721
Please. Come in.

531
00:38:36.690 --> 00:38:40.735
I was forced into marriage
with a very powerful warlord.

532
00:38:40.736 --> 00:38:43.196
He was cruel to me.

533
00:38:43.197 --> 00:38:44.906
And there was nowhere
in China I could run

534
00:38:44.907 --> 00:38:47.116
where he wouldn't find me.

535
00:38:47.117 --> 00:38:51.621
And so I started secretly
bringing weapons from his home

536
00:38:51.622 --> 00:38:53.165
to the market and selling them.

537
00:38:54.041 --> 00:38:56.667
He had so many.
Never missed them.

538
00:38:56.668 --> 00:38:58.503
And eventually. I
had enough money

539
00:38:58.504 --> 00:38:59.838
for a ticket to America.

540
00:39:01.548 --> 00:39:02.758
My Lord.

541
00:39:05.260 --> 00:39:08.221
What would he have done
if he had caught you?

542
00:39:08.222 --> 00:39:11.099
He would have killed me.

543
00:39:11.100 --> 00:39:13.226
Oh. but if I had stayed.

544
00:39:13.227 --> 00:39:15.479
he would have eventually
killed me anyway.

545
00:39:17.231 --> 00:39:18.941
Or I would have killed myself.

546
00:39:20.526 --> 00:39:23.862
And now you have
men working for you.

547
00:39:26.573 --> 00:39:29.659
I have to imagine there
were almost no opportunities

548
00:39:29.660 --> 00:39:31.410
for a Chinese woman here.

549
00:39:31.411 --> 00:39:33.579
It's really very impressive.

550
00:39:33.580 --> 00:39:35.581
How did you do it?

551
00:39:35.582 --> 00:39:38.000
Well. I just have
one rule. really.

552
00:39:38.001 --> 00:39:40.838
But it's... it's served me well.

553
00:39:42.506 --> 00:39:43.715
Be smarter.

554
00:39:44.508 --> 00:39:45.551
Than whom?

555
00:39:47.010 --> 00:39:48.011
Than the men.

556
00:40:09.741 --> 00:40:11.618
Thank you for having
us in your home.

557
00:40:13.162 --> 00:40:15.538
It was so inspiring
to hear your story.

558
00:40:15.539 --> 00:40:18.457
We're having a small
reception in a few days.

559
00:40:18.458 --> 00:40:19.876
Just some close friends.

560
00:40:19.877 --> 00:40:23.921
But I think they would
love to hear your story.

561
00:40:23.922 --> 00:40:26.048
And it would be such
a unique opportunity

562
00:40:26.049 --> 00:40:27.508
for people to meet

563
00:40:27.509 --> 00:40:30.970
a truly exceptional
Chinese woman

564
00:40:30.971 --> 00:40:32.806
who has overcome so much.

565
00:40:35.934 --> 00:40:38.311
You're inviting me to your home?

566
00:40:38.312 --> 00:40:39.604
Yes.

567
00:40:39.605 --> 00:40:41.606
And I insist you come.

568
00:40:41.607 --> 00:40:43.733
The details are on the card.

569
00:40:43.734 --> 00:40:47.029
Goodbye.

570
00:40:55.370 --> 00:40:57.288
Chao did well.

571
00:40:57.289 --> 00:41:00.208
That group was much
better than the last one.

572
00:41:00.209 --> 00:41:02.836
Our new house is already
paying dividends.

573
00:41:06.757 --> 00:41:08.217
You disapprove.

574
00:41:09.384 --> 00:41:11.135
I just don't like the
way they look at you.

575
00:41:11.136 --> 00:41:15.056
They are fascinated with us.

576
00:41:15.057 --> 00:41:17.141
If I can gain their trust.

577
00:41:17.142 --> 00:41:21.562
I can make them see us as
people to do business with.

578
00:41:21.563 --> 00:41:23.314
Chinatown is getting smaller.

579
00:41:23.315 --> 00:41:26.567
We need to expand beyond it.

580
00:41:26.568 --> 00:41:29.112
Out in the pond. not
everyone hates us.

581
00:41:31.240 --> 00:41:33.741
They'll never
treat us as equals.

582
00:41:33.742 --> 00:41:34.951
No.

583
00:41:34.952 --> 00:41:37.703
But the ducks are greedy.

584
00:41:37.704 --> 00:41:41.041
And our money is as
good as anyone else's.

585
00:41:52.344 --> 00:41:54.136
Does it still hurt?

586
00:41:54.137 --> 00:41:56.347
Not so much.

587
00:41:56.348 --> 00:41:58.808
I move fine. no?

588
00:41:58.809 --> 00:42:01.228
Yes. you do.

589
00:42:04.898 --> 00:42:08.693
By the way. I think I may
have found another property.

590
00:42:08.694 --> 00:42:11.737
Just a few miles from here.

591
00:42:11.738 --> 00:42:13.823
Another one?

592
00:42:13.824 --> 00:42:16.659
We could help more girls.

593
00:42:16.660 --> 00:42:19.203
Maybe I buy it with you.

594
00:42:19.204 --> 00:42:21.123
If you want to. yes.

595
00:42:23.500 --> 00:42:25.835
It's very nice here.

596
00:42:25.836 --> 00:42:26.877
With you.

597
00:42:26.878 --> 00:42:28.671
Yeah?

598
00:42:28.672 --> 00:42:31.090
Well. maybe you should
consider staying longer.

599
00:42:31.091 --> 00:42:34.427
Longer? How long?

600
00:42:34.428 --> 00:42:37.847
Always.

601
00:42:37.848 --> 00:42:39.181
Always?

602
00:42:39.182 --> 00:42:41.183
Why not?

603
00:42:41.184 --> 00:42:44.186
You're here so much
these days as it is.

604
00:42:44.187 --> 00:42:48.024
Hmm. I have business
in Chinatown.

605
00:42:48.025 --> 00:42:49.610
This is better business.

606
00:42:52.362 --> 00:42:55.156
Maybe it's time to
think about a change.

607
00:42:55.157 --> 00:42:56.575
Huh?

608
00:42:59.494 --> 00:43:00.829
Maybe.

609
00:43:44.790 --> 00:43:46.917
You're getting slow
in your old age.

610
00:43:51.213 --> 00:43:52.547
You want some company?

611
00:43:54.508 --> 00:43:55.675
You sure you're up for it?

612
00:43:57.928 --> 00:44:00.221
I'm sure I'm not.

613
00:44:00.222 --> 00:44:03.516
My ribs still remember
the last time you hit me.

614
00:44:03.517 --> 00:44:05.476
Mm-hmm.

615
00:44:05.477 --> 00:44:06.645
I have a better idea.

616
00:44:13.902 --> 00:44:16.278
Look. you know if
I had the choice.

617
00:44:16.279 --> 00:44:18.614
I would not have
joined the Long Zii.

618
00:44:18.615 --> 00:44:22.243
But I have to say.
if nothing else.

619
00:44:22.244 --> 00:44:24.328
it's nice to be your
brother in arms again.

620
00:44:24.329 --> 00:44:27.164
It's been too long since
we fought on the same side.

621
00:44:27.165 --> 00:44:28.999
I agree. brother.

622
00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:30.251
Our friendship kept the peace

623
00:44:30.252 --> 00:44:31.627
between our tongs
for many years.

624
00:44:31.628 --> 00:44:33.504
Yes. it did.

625
00:44:33.505 --> 00:44:35.424
If only you had a friend
like me in the Hop Wei.

626
00:44:37.884 --> 00:44:39.552
The thing is. the Hop Wei
are less of a threat today

627
00:44:39.553 --> 00:44:41.178
than they were yesterday.

628
00:44:41.179 --> 00:44:42.638
Maybe.

629
00:44:42.639 --> 00:44:44.807
But Ah Sahm is no
less dangerous.

630
00:44:44.808 --> 00:44:46.851
Don't worry about Ah Sahm.

631
00:44:46.852 --> 00:44:48.727
The beauty of no longer
being the head of a tong

632
00:44:48.728 --> 00:44:50.522
is that I don't
worry about anything.

633
00:44:51.982 --> 00:44:53.525
I leave that to you.

634
00:45:05.078 --> 00:45:07.997
You know.

635
00:45:07.998 --> 00:45:09.707
we all believed
you would take over

636
00:45:09.708 --> 00:45:12.334
when Long Zii died.

637
00:45:12.335 --> 00:45:15.172
Wasn't that your understanding
with the old man?

638
00:45:17.048 --> 00:45:18.549
Mai Ling has done
more for the tong

639
00:45:18.550 --> 00:45:22.386
than I ever could have.

640
00:45:22.387 --> 00:45:23.638
I'm not a leader.

641
00:45:29.436 --> 00:45:30.937
To Long Zii.

642
00:45:36.193 --> 00:45:37.486
To the Long Zii.

643
00:45:45.952 --> 00:45:47.370
Are you kidding me?

644
00:46:11.686 --> 00:46:15.689
Just wanted you to know that
I'm still holding onto it.

645
00:46:15.690 --> 00:46:18.693
In case. you know. you
ever wanna come back.

646
00:46:21.446 --> 00:46:22.947
I could really use you.

647
00:46:22.948 --> 00:46:26.116
what with this
new chief and all.

648
00:46:26.117 --> 00:46:28.661
I thought you were supposed
to be the new chief.

649
00:46:28.662 --> 00:46:30.579
I thought so too.

650
00:46:30.580 --> 00:46:33.583
Mr. Buckley felt otherwise.

651
00:46:36.002 --> 00:46:37.337
I'm sorry. Bill.

652
00:46:39.756 --> 00:46:42.424
But I'm not coming back.

653
00:46:42.425 --> 00:46:44.261
Now you sound like my wife.

654
00:46:47.347 --> 00:46:49.099
She's still at her sister's?

655
00:46:51.560 --> 00:46:54.728
The plan was. I
was gonna be chief

656
00:46:54.729 --> 00:46:58.816
and out of Chinatown.
and she'd come home.

657
00:46:58.817 --> 00:47:01.361
Now. I have no idea
how to get her back.

658
00:47:02.529 --> 00:47:04.196
Bill.

659
00:47:04.197 --> 00:47:06.031
It's bad enough
you drink for free.

660
00:47:06.032 --> 00:47:07.199
If you start recruiting.

661
00:47:07.200 --> 00:47:09.660
I'm gonna have to
break your legs.

662
00:47:09.661 --> 00:47:12.079
Yes. ma'am.

663
00:47:12.080 --> 00:47:14.456
Do I need to worry about you?

664
00:47:14.457 --> 00:47:16.166
No more than usual.

665
00:47:16.167 --> 00:47:17.377
Good.

666
00:47:22.882 --> 00:47:25.009
That's a good woman
you've got there.

667
00:47:25.010 --> 00:47:27.511
Sweet as stolen honey.

668
00:47:27.512 --> 00:47:30.180
But she can ride
the rough string.

669
00:47:30.181 --> 00:47:32.224
Right.

670
00:47:32.225 --> 00:47:34.227
I assume that was
you agreeing with me.

671
00:47:37.480 --> 00:47:39.190
I'll be seeing you.

672
00:47:45.155 --> 00:47:46.448
She'll come back. Bill.

673
00:47:47.657 --> 00:47:49.617
Just give her time.

674
00:47:49.618 --> 00:47:51.620
That's what she said about you.

675
00:47:53.830 --> 00:47:57.334
Turns out. you're both idiots.

676
00:48:07.260 --> 00:48:08.511
What's this?

677
00:48:09.346 --> 00:48:11.306
Those are your
new lumber prices.

678
00:48:13.224 --> 00:48:14.976
I paid Sanderson a
visit last night.

679
00:48:16.811 --> 00:48:17.651
What'd you do to him?

680
00:48:19.981 --> 00:48:22.566
I negotiated.

681
00:48:22.567 --> 00:48:24.944
And now you have the
margins to hire Irish labor.

682
00:48:27.489 --> 00:48:29.073
He'll honor these numbers?

683
00:48:29.074 --> 00:48:30.992
He will.

684
00:48:33.703 --> 00:48:36.288
They don't completely
bridge the gap.

685
00:48:36.289 --> 00:48:39.917
but they do give me
room to maneuver.

686
00:48:39.918 --> 00:48:44.922
You understand your men will be
working alongside the Chinese.

687
00:48:44.923 --> 00:48:46.632
Will they agree to that?

688
00:48:46.633 --> 00:48:49.218
How many men?

689
00:48:49.219 --> 00:48:52.930
15.

690
00:48:52.931 --> 00:48:53.932
20.

691
00:48:56.976 --> 00:48:58.061
Done.

692
00:49:21.710 --> 00:49:23.127
Good evening.

693
00:49:23.128 --> 00:49:25.796
What the fuck is this?

694
00:49:25.797 --> 00:49:28.090
Watch out.

695
00:49:28.091 --> 00:49:29.967
Watch out for
what. motherfucker?

696
00:49:29.968 --> 00:49:31.135
Huh?

697
00:49:31.136 --> 00:49:32.303
That.

698
00:49:41.354 --> 00:49:42.230
Hey. you!

699
00:49:49.362 --> 00:49:50.571
Oh.

700
00:49:50.572 --> 00:49:51.613
Hey. asshole.

701
00:49:51.614 --> 00:49:53.031
Think you're gonna rob us?

702
00:49:53.032 --> 00:49:54.872
Wait. wait. wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait. wait!

703
00:49:58.079 --> 00:49:59.247
Oh. God!

704
00:50:07.589 --> 00:50:08.840
You get what you pay for.

705
00:50:11.718 --> 00:50:12.598
So where's this money?

706
00:50:17.724 --> 00:50:19.976
- It was right here.
- Are you kidding me?

707
00:50:52.592 --> 00:50:54.093
I don't see any money. Chao.

708
00:50:56.346 --> 00:50:58.389
What the hell is this?

709
00:51:02.727 --> 00:51:03.978
Something better.

710
00:51:05.730 --> 00:51:06.970
The fuck are you talking about?

711
00:51:09.234 --> 00:51:12.986
You know. my father always said.

712
00:51:12.987 --> 00:51:15.781
the best way to make money...

713
00:51:15.782 --> 00:51:18.034
is to make money.

713
00:51:19.305 --> 00:52:19.390
